  "body": "### Description\n\nATM, the `@Param*` annotations are allowed on resource/endpoint and beanparam properties, but the `@Rest*` parameters are not allowed there.\r\nI'm not even sure the beanparam support handles them on the server (perhaps the TCK tests that?). But the client has support for them.\r\n\r\nWe should:\r\n\r\n- Allow `@Rest*` annotations on properties, to be symmetrical with the `@*Param` annotations\r\n- Validate that they work on resource/endpoint (for the server) and beanparam properties (client and server)\r\n- Also figure out if they should be applied on getters or setters, because the spec is very vague about this.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
